# Toggle Button Design - Frontend Changes

## Summary
Implemented a modern theme toggle button with sun/moon icons positioned in the top-right corner of the header. The toggle allows users to switch between dark and light themes with smooth animations and maintains their preference in localStorage.

## Files Modified

### 1. frontend/index.html
**Changes:**
- Modified header structure to include a header-content wrapper with flex layout
- Added theme toggle button with sun and moon SVG icons
- Made header visible (was previously hidden)
- Added proper semantic structure with aria-label for accessibility

**Key additions:**
- `<div class="header-content">` wrapper for flex layout
- `<button class="theme-toggle" id="themeToggle" aria-label="Toggle theme">` with icon structure
- Sun and moon SVG icons with proper viewBox and stroke styling

### 2. frontend/style.css
**Changes:**
- Made header visible and styled with proper padding and borders
- Added complete CSS for theme toggle button including:
  - Modern toggle switch design with track and slider
  - Smooth animations using cubic-bezier transitions
  - Icon rotation and opacity transitions
  - Hover and focus states for accessibility
  - Active state styling when toggled
- Updated responsive design for mobile devices
- Maintained design consistency with existing color scheme

**Key CSS additions:**
- `.header-content` - Flex layout for header with space-between
- `.theme-toggle` - Main button styling with focus management
- `.toggle-track` - Background track for the toggle switch
- `.toggle-slider` - Animated slider element that moves on toggle
- `.sun-icon` / `.moon-icon` - Icon styling with rotation animations
- Mobile responsive adjustments for header layout

### 3. frontend/script.js
**Changes:**
- Added themeToggle DOM element reference
- Added theme toggle event listeners (click and keyboard navigation)
- Implemented complete theme system with:
  - `initializeThemeToggle()` - Loads saved preference and sets initial state
  - `toggleTheme()` - Handles theme switching and localStorage persistence
  - `applyTheme()` - Dynamically updates CSS custom properties
- Added keyboard accessibility (Enter and Space key support)
- Theme preference persistence using localStorage

**Key functions added:**
- `initializeThemeToggle()` - Sets up initial theme state
- `toggleTheme()` - Main toggle function with state management
- `applyTheme(theme)` - Dynamic CSS variable updates for light/dark themes

## Features Implemented

### 1. Visual Design
- ✅ Modern toggle switch design that fits existing aesthetic
- ✅ Sun/moon icon system with smooth transitions
- ✅ Positioned in top-right corner of header
- ✅ Consistent with existing color scheme and styling

### 2. Animations
- ✅ Smooth slider transition (300ms cubic-bezier)
- ✅ Icon rotation and opacity changes
- ✅ Hover effects with color and border transitions
- ✅ Focus states for accessibility

### 3. Accessibility
- ✅ Proper ARIA labels that update based on current state
- ✅ Keyboard navigation support (Enter and Space keys)
- ✅ Focus indicators with box-shadow
- ✅ Semantic button element

### 4. Functionality
- ✅ Theme switching between dark and light modes
- ✅ LocalStorage persistence of user preference
- ✅ Dynamic CSS custom property updates
- ✅ Proper state management and DOM updates

### 5. Responsive Design
- ✅ Mobile-friendly layout adjustments
- ✅ Header stacks vertically on small screens
- ✅ Toggle button repositioned appropriately

## Theme Colors

### Dark Theme (Default)
- Background: #0f172a
- Surface: #1e293b
- Text Primary: #f1f5f9
- Text Secondary: #94a3b8
- Border: #334155

### Light Theme
- Background: #ffffff
- Surface: #f8fafc
- Text Primary: #0f172a
- Text Secondary: #475569
- Border: #e2e8f0

## User Experience
- Users can click the toggle to switch themes
- Theme preference is remembered across sessions
- Visual feedback with smooth animations
- Accessible for keyboard users
- Consistent with modern UI patterns